body:
Hi,

output port clocking block delay defined as `1step` is not supported:

```
interface ahb_ifc #(int P_DATA_WIDTH);

  //***** Master driven signals *****
  // Clock
  logic                    hclk;
  // Reset
  logic                    hresetn;
  // Address
  wire [            31:0]  haddr;
  // Read/Write
  wire                     hwrite;
  // Data size
  wire [             2:0]  hsize;
  // Burst type
  wire [             2:0]  hburst;
  // Protection control
  wire [             3:0]  hprot;
  // Transfer type
  wire [             1:0]  htrans;
  // Lock
  wire                     hmastlock;
  // Write data
  wire [P_DATA_WIDTH-1:0]  hwdata;
  // Slave select
  wire                     hsel;

  //***** Slave driven signals *****
  // Slave Ready Status
  wire                     hready;
  // Slave Response
  wire                     hresp;
  // Read data
  wire [P_DATA_WIDTH-1:0]  hrdata;

  // Clocking block for master driver
  clocking cb_m_drv @(posedge hclk);
    default input #1step output #1step;
    input  hready, hresp, hrdata;
    output haddr, hwrite, hsize, hwdata;
    output hburst, hprot, htrans, hmastlock, hsel;
  endclocking

endinterface : ahb_ifc
```

What output from that test indicates it is wrong, and what is the correct or expected output?  (Or, please make test self-checking if possible.)

```
%Error: t_clocking_output_1step/t_clocking_output_1step.sv:44:33: 1step not allowed as output skew
   44 |     default input #1step output #1step;
      |                                 ^
        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html?v=5.042 for more assistance.
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?

```
verilator --cc t_clocking_output_1step/t_clocking_output_1step.sv
```

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?

5.042

What OS and distribution are you using?

Linux runner4.tropic.dev.hq.sldev.cz 4.18.0-553.58.1.el8_10.x86_64 #1 SMP Thu Jun 12 14:27:07 EDT 2025 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux

May we assist you in trying to fix this in Verilator yourself?

Yes, this would be appreciated.

